-- в”Ђв”Ђ Zuddl в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Modular B2B event management platform for virtual, hybrid, and in-person conferences, field events, and webinars with CRM-integrated analytics.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom pricing based on event format and attendee volume$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2020, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Zuddl Review: Event Management Platform Features and Pricing (2026)$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Explore Zuddl's virtual, hybrid, and in-person event platform, including Studio production, booths, networking, CRM integration, and custom pricing.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Zuddl is a modular B2B event management platform for virtual, hybrid, and in-person events, founded in 2020 by Bharath Varma and Vedha Sayyaparaju and headquartered in San Francisco, with additional operations in Bangalore, India. The company went through Y Combinator's 2020 batch and raised a 13.35 million dollar Series A round led by Alpha Wave Incubation and Qualcomm Ventures, with participation from GrowX Ventures and Waveform Ventures, bringing total funding to approximately 15.5 million dollars. Zuddl targets B2B marketers, associations, and conference organizers running events ranging from small webinars to large-scale conferences with 100 to over 25,000 attendees. The platform's Studio module offers broadcast-quality live streaming with multi-speaker sessions, branded overlays, and real-time production control, letting organizers produce TV-like broadcasts without external production crews. For virtual and hybrid events, Zuddl provides customizable exhibitor booths with downloadable content, video chat, and lead capture forms, alongside networking tools such as breakout rooms, one-on-one meeting scheduling, gamification, and AI-powered attendee matchmaking. A core differentiator is deep, bi-directional CRM and marketing automation integration with platforms like Salesforce, HubSpot, Marketo, and Pardot, syncing attendee engagement and conversion data directly into go-to-market systems. Organizers can fully brand registration pages, virtual event venues, and mobile event apps to match their company identity. Zuddl's pricing is not publicly listed and varies by event format: third-party sources cite starting points such as roughly 80 dollars per month for entry-level use, around 10,000 dollars per year for Zuddl Webinar, and around 12,000 dollars per year for Zuddl Conferences, with virtual event pricing commonly based on annual attendee volume rather than per-event or per-registration fees. Prospective customers generally need to request a custom quote based on their specific event program needs.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '36a4b760-5ccb-4498-b325-7b29a847d7cf';

